@*
    ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    BnStarterPage — your app's first screen, and its "/" route (the page the
    shell boots into). Registered as "BnStarterPage" in AppPages.All.

    A .razor class is named by its FILE name, so this file IS the
    BnStarterPage the manifest names. Rename it and you rename the page —
    in which case AppPages.All and MainActivity's `?: "BnStarterPage"`
    fallback both need the new name (the BlazorNative repo pins that pair).

    THE SUPPORTED SUBSET (the laws this shell actually enforces):
      · Bn* components only — there is no DOM here. <div>/<span>/<p> are not
        widgets and will not render; the BN analyzers flag the common cases.
      · Components referenced in markup must be PUBLIC.
      · @bind / @onclick need `@using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Web`
        in scope — _Imports.razor has it, and it is load-bearing: without it
        the compiler emits them as LITERAL MARKUP, with zero diagnostics and
        a green build, silently dead on a native shell.

    Shape:
      BnView          the root — padding + a background colour
       ├─ BnText      the title
       ├─ BnText      the live echo of `name`
       ├─ BnInput     two-way bound to `name`
       └─ BnButton    a counter, proving the event wire round-trips
    ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*@
<BnView BackgroundColor="#FFFFFF" Padding="16">
    <BnText Text="Hello from BlazorNative" FontSize="24" />

    <BnText Text="@Greeting" FontSize="16" />
    <BnInput @bind-Value="name" />

    <BnButton Label="@($"Tapped {taps} time(s)")" OnClick="OnTap" />
</BnView>

@code {
    private string name = "world";
    private int taps;

    private string Greeting => $"Hello, {name}!";

    // Sync-completing on the inline dispatcher: by the time this returns the
    // re-render has been delivered to the shell.
    private void OnTap() => taps++;
}
